[[File:Belvedere Apartments.JPG|thumb|Belvedere Apartments in Columbia, Missouri]] '''Belvedere Apartments''' is a well-preserved [[Spanish Colonial Revival architecture|Spanish Colonial Revival]]-style apartment building located at 206 Hitt Street in downtown [[Columbia, Missouri]]. Built in 1927, the building was designed by notable architect, [[Nelle Peters]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Engel|first=Elizabeth|title=Nelle E. Peters (1884 - 1974)|url=http://shs.umsystem.edu/historicmissourians/name/p/peters/index.html|publisher=State Historical Society of Missouri|accessdate=22 January 2014}}</ref> The building was added to Columbia's Notable Buildings List in 2008<ref>{{cite news|last=Hughes|first=Kat|title=Honoring historic places|url=http://archive.columbiatribune.com/2008/feb/20080207news007.asp|accessdate=22 January 2014|newspaper=Columbia Tribune|date=7 February 2008|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201180120/http://archive.columbiatribune.com/2008/feb/20080207news007.asp|archivedate=1 February 2014|df=}}</ref> and is a possible candidate for the [[National Register of Historic Places]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Final Survey Report Locust Historic Study Area|url=http://www.dnr.mo.gov/shpo/survey/BOAS001-R.pdf|publisher=State Historic Preservation Office of Missouri’s Department of Natural Resources|accessdate=22 January 2014|author=Ruth Keenoy|author2=Terri Foley}}</ref> As of 2014, the apartments are being rented by private owners.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dumasapartmentscolumbiamo.wordpress.com/the-belvedere/|title=BELVEDERE BUILDING|accessdate=22 January 2014}}</ref>
